snippet.title: Moose Encounter in the Boundary Waters Canoe Area
snippet.description:
My dog and I encounter a Bull Moose in the Boundary Waters Canoe Area on a 10 day solo trip. Monty, my dog, did very well at keeping quiet but was jumping for joy and doing circles in the back of my canoe.

This video is a small segment from our full 10 day adventure. Each part is linked below!

Part 1!: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2OQuCGCoMWE
Part 2!: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gd6pEmjNo-w
Part 3!: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FgmTyh2Bw1o

Don't miss out! Subscribe!

snippet.title: The Dog Treat Song
snippet.description:
A song about a dog and a treat.

Part of the reason I uploaded this video was to raise awareness of a condition called, "Dog Bloat." The dog in this video, Hachi, passed away due to this condition.

Dog bloat caused Hachi's stomach to flip, which is called, "Gastric Dilatation Volvulus." We did all we could to save him and even after surgery we lost him. Learn the signs as early detection is key in saving your dogs life. Ask your vet about preventing this condition. If we had known more, he'd still be he with us.

This was actually a practice run for this song but we never got a chance to do another take.

Thank you for watching!

Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/matthewposa/

snippet.title: Lake Superior Otters Try to Steal My Fish at Isle Royale
snippet.description:
During one of the last days of our first 2 week camping trip on Isle Royale, we had to paddle about 8 miles. During that time I caught a 10 lb king salmon and had paddled at least 6 miles with it on my stringer and it created a ton of drag.

When we got to camp, I tied off my fish to the dock and put it down in the water to keep it cold. When I came back later to check on it, it was gone. I knew the culprit, Otters.

I went out fishing the next day and caught 2 Lake Trout. This time I knew better than to leave them near the dock, so we walked down to the water, far away from the dock, near our camp and tied them to a tree.

About an hour goes by and Funk sees the tree they are tied to shaking and screams, "POSA!!! OTTERS!!!!" We both run down to the water and this is what we find.

Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/matthewposa/

snippet.title: Lake Superior Windstorm October 24th 2017
snippet.description:
I put on my rain gear and walked around Presque Isle park in Marquette, Michigan during a windstorm on October 24th 2017. 

I took extreme caution while recording making sure I had good footing and did not stand where water was sweeping.

I know the risks involved but this was something I wanted to see with my own eyes.

Follow me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/matthewposa/
